15/03/2011
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Greek Cypriots Loizos Afxentiou and Yiannakis Matsis, who were arrested on Saturday (March 12th) for trespassing on a military area in the northern part of the island, were released on Monday after being fined by a military court there. 
Each of them was sentenced to pay 907 euros for entering the zone without permission from Turkish forces. 
Two Polish members of the European Parliament were also detained on Saturday, but were later released. 
The group entered the zone to visit destroyed Orthodox churches there. 
(Imerisia - 15/03/11; Famagusta Gazette - 14/03/11)
